============================================================
  DL MONITOR SYSTEM — BUILD & DEPLOY GUIDE
============================================================

FOLDER STRUCTURE
----------------
DL_PC\
    process_files.py      <- Main loop, reads logs, detects fails
    register_logger.py    <- Saves record, stamps stop time, sends signal
    network_sender.py     <- TCP client to Main PC
    stop_tracker.py       <- Tracks last stop time per DL

MAIN_PC\
    main_pc_listener.py   <- TCP server + pywinauto EXE automation

BUILD_SCRIPTS\
    build_DL_PC.bat       <- Builds dl_monitor.exe
    build_MAIN_PC.bat     <- Builds main_pc_listener.exe
    README.txt            <- This file


============================================================
STEP 1 — EDIT CONFIGURATION (before building)
============================================================

In DL_PC\register_logger.py:
    MAIN_PC_IP       = "192.168.1.100"   <- set to your Main PC's IP
    MAIN_PC_PORT     = 9999
    LOG_REGISTER_DIR = r"C:\log_register"

In DL_PC\process_files.py:
    LOG_DIRECTORY = r"C:\logs"           <- folder where log files are

In MAIN_PC\main_pc_listener.py:
    LISTEN_PORT     = 9999               <- must match MAIN_PC_PORT above
    EXE_TITLE       = "YourAppTitle"     <- partial title of the EXE window
    SETUP_WIN_TITLE = "Setup Manual"     <- title of the sub-window
    CLICK_DELAY     = 0.6               <- increase if EXE is slow


============================================================
STEP 2 — FIND EXE CONTROL NAMES (Main PC only)
============================================================

You need the exact button/checkbox names inside the EXE.
Do this ONCE before building:

1. Install Python + pywinauto on any PC temporarily:
       pip install pywinauto

2. Open the EXE on Main PC so it is running.

3. Run:
       python main_pc_listener.py spy

4. It prints all control names. Note the exact names for:
       - Stop button
       - Save button
       - Start button
       - DL checkboxes (e.g. "DL01", "DL_01", "Line 1", etc.)

5. Update main_pc_listener.py  child_window(title=...) calls
   to match those exact names.


============================================================
STEP 3 — BUILD THE EXE FILES
============================================================

You need Python on ONE machine temporarily (can be any laptop).
After building, the .exe files run anywhere with NO Python needed.

--- Build dl_monitor.exe (for DL PC) ---
1. Copy the entire DL_PC\ folder to a machine with Python
2. Also copy BUILD_SCRIPTS\build_DL_PC.bat into the DL_PC\ folder
3. Double-click build_DL_PC.bat
4. Find the output at:  DL_PC\dist\dl_monitor.exe

--- Build main_pc_listener.exe (for Main PC) ---
1. Copy the entire MAIN_PC\ folder to a machine with Python
2. Also copy BUILD_SCRIPTS\build_MAIN_PC.bat into the MAIN_PC\ folder
3. Double-click build_MAIN_PC.bat
4. Find the output at:  MAIN_PC\dist\main_pc_listener.exe


============================================================
STEP 4 — DEPLOY
============================================================

On DL PC:
    1. Copy dl_monitor.exe to any folder e.g. C:\DL_Monitor\
    2. Double-click to run — it scans every 30 seconds automatically
    3. To auto-start on boot:
       - Press Win+R → shell:startup
       - Drop a shortcut to dl_monitor.exe there

On Main PC:
    1. Copy main_pc_listener.exe to any folder e.g. C:\DL_Monitor\
    2. Double-click to run — it waits silently for signals from DL PC
    3. To auto-start on boot:
       - Press Win+R → shell:startup
       - Drop a shortcut to main_pc_listener.exe there
    4. Allow it through Windows Firewall if prompted
       (it needs to receive on port 9999)


============================================================
STEP 5 — VERIFY IT WORKS
============================================================

On Main PC — confirm listener is running:
    You should see in the console:
    "Listening on 0.0.0.0:9999 — ready for DL PC signals."

On DL PC — confirm it connects:
    When a DL hits 3 fails, you should see in the console:
    "DL03 STOPPED | Cycle Fails = 3 | Fail Rate = xx.xx%"

On Main PC — confirm automation ran:
    "DL03: Clicked Stop"
    "DL03: Unchecked"
    "DL03: Clicked Save"
    "DL03: Clicked Start — automation complete"

Log files are saved to C:\log_register\ on DL PC.


============================================================
FAIL COUNTER RESET LOGIC
============================================================

Each DL has an independent counter that resets after every stop:

  Fail 1, 2, 3  ->  STOP triggered  ->  counter resets to 0
  (Main PC restarts DL)
  Fail 4, 5     ->  count = 2, nothing happens
  Fail 6        ->  count = 3  ->  STOP triggered again

Old FAILs before the stop are never counted again.
Each stop saves a new file:  DL03_20260520_stop1.json
                              DL03_20260520_stop2.json  etc.

============================================================
